caption: Amazing egg sandwiches! 😋
During this pandemic I like to support local vendors and restaurants. This was the worse chicken sandwich I’ve ever had. The construction didn’t bother me as much as the poor service.
Incredible food and customer service. Highly recommend the fried chicken sandwich.
Delicious fried chicken sandwich!
Love their pastries and probably the best breakfast sandwich in the neighborhood
Incredible place. Makes the neighborhood tick! Happy vibes and superb pastry.
One of the most delicious egg sandwiches in a neighborhood full of excellent ones.
OTWAY family owned LOCAL excellent restaurant = Pls support! Taco thursday is great.
Breakfast sandwich was tasty, coffee was great, service was okay
(Translated by Google) Excellent croissant  (Original) Excellent croissant
Staff was friendly and they were being pretty responsible with their health and safety measure. Unfortunately the food wasnt great.

Otway is awesome and my go to spot for coffee, brunch, pastries etc. The woman who owns it is really nice and friendly and most importantly puts so much love in all aspects of the place and it really shows. They have awesome outdoor seating now too! If you’re into good bread try their rye bread.

Ordered brunch takeout: Breakfast sandwich, brisket sandwich, and crispy potatoes. Only thing good were crispy potatoes. Breakfast sandwich had too many eggs and bacon was undercooked. Brisket was tough (overcooked) and had an odd gravy like taste that didn’t meld well with other sandwich ingredients and generally didn’t taste well. Trashed 3/4 of both sandwiches which is a pity given prices.

Brunch: fried chicken sandwich 👌, egg sandwich is good but be specific about how you want your yolk cooked (or get scrambled), the cruller donut behind the counter has to be one of the best I've ever had (not sure if made in-house or not). Get polenta if you want a rich and creamy update to country style grits, complete with gorgeous wild mushrooms. It gets crowded on Sundays, so go early or on Saturday.
Great food, service and drinks. The tenderloin was done perfectly. One of our party loves duck, ordered it and said it was the best duck she ever had. Highly recommend.

Love the atmosphere and aesthetics here. Real hidden gem. We always have a lovely time here and have enjoyed all the food we’ve had (only been for brunch/breakfast). Great coffee and pastries and especially love all the little antique spoons!

The food here is incredible (both brunch and dinner) but expect a wait. We showed up for brunch as they were opening- had to wait an hour until the kitchen opened and then another 45 min for our meal. We would have been upset but the food was so good we had to try it again. We came back for oysters and snacks- still had to wait awhile for food but when it finally emerged, it was delicious!

Came in for work related purposes and was delighted by the ambiance and super kind server. Had a pumpkin pecan cake slice and it was the best I’ve ever had. I was reluctant to try it at first because I’m not a nuts kind of girl but did anyway and I ate every bit of cake and nut there was and wanted more. It was a perfect balance of sweet and yummy! The vibe is super chill and relaxing!

- Late seating (with reservation) - Cold food - Overpriced food and drinks - Tiny portions (The “cheese plate” was a single piece of cheese less than half an inch wide) - Weird flavors and textures  We came here for new years’ eve and had the prix fixe menu at $75 a piece (not including drinks). Now I know it’s a prix fixe so they are trying to simplify things in the kitchen and turn a profit but we got very little food and ALL OF IT CAME OUT COLD including the tenderloin and fish entrees. We let our server know and they took all of our entrees back and they brought them back out still cold! They gave us some prosecco when I asked if there was anything they could do for us but we ended up paying $130+ per person and went home hungry. It’s frustrating because the atmosphere was charming and our waiter tried. I have never paid more for less food. All they had to do to make our night amazing was feed us something warm, well seasoned, and filling.

I got a coffee and I put a milk at 12:00 on 12/30. The milk was old and didn’t mix well. So, I asked the guy to change them but he refused. He said just mixed it. I’ve never had this experience in other cafe. They always changed and gave me a new coffee.  I feel very bad. I don’t want to think this is racism, but I feel that way. Low service employees.

Food was OK. Expensive for what it is. Took a long time to get food at the table. Received the wrong item. Restaurant did adjust the $$ amount once brought to their attention. Service could be better.
The food was incredible. The service was attentive and lovely. What a great place.
Lovely staff (esp during Sat brunch rush).

The coffee was delicious and the pastries are fresh. The golden raisin scone was delicious and moist. The savory biscuit was ok.  However, my mother, sister and I agreed the bun and almond croissant would not be a repeat order.
Delicious food, lovely atmosphere, and thoughtful wait staff.

Went on a saturday morning for brunch. Restaurant wasn't full but the food took a long time and didn't come out until we asked for it to be checked on. We ordered chicken liver mousse, almond croissant, breakfast platter and blt. Taste wise everything was average and nothing special. The almond croissant was quite good though.

Otway is one of my favorite restaurants in Brooklyn. It's casual in it's amotsphere and demeanor, but it is sophisticated in its cuisine and service. If you want food that you will want to talk about for weeks, go to Otway. I suggest it to everyone
Great food, amazing bread.
Generally great, very detailed. Do not like the deviled eggs though

Service was impeccable for me and my 2 yr old granddaughter for brunch at noon on a Tuesday. Our waiter was very gracious and attentive. Perfect cup of coffee (americano). My hot chicken sandwich was great - very different from anything I've had before. Yogurt,  fruit and house made granola for her...she loved it. Highly recommended!

French bistro in the neighborhood. Simple food, fairly well done. Good service at the bar but table service could use some polishing up. Good bread, which sounds weird to say, but for Brooklyn that’s an oasis. As other folks have mentioned, the environment in the restaurant is excellent. Probably the best value happy hour in Clinton Hill.

(Translated by Google) Arriving at work I found this old typewriter, I call myself a lot of attention because they are articles that are not used. But they were used by our grandparents and are part of our pasts.  (Original) Llegando al trabajo me encontré esta antigua maquina de escribir, me llamo mucho la atención ya que son artículos que no se usan. Pero que los utilizaron nuestros abuelos y son parte de nuestros pasados.

Cute little French-adjacent place for dinner or drinks. Go M-F 5:30-7:30 for LE BINGE: happy hour pricing on drinks & $15 for a dozen oysters. Great ambiance and food overall but be aware: It’s a very small space (read: hard to maneuver in) and not every cocktail is subject to happy hour pricing.
Cute vibe, a little loud, good chicken sando
Delicious food and excellent service
Great prices, great food! Glad we came across it today.

Came for the breakfast sandwich that had been storied to me in one way or another as THE BEST breakfast sandwich in Brooklyn. Spoiler alert: it's very, very good. I wasn't able to go all the way out on the gangplank and say that it's THE BEST, but it's certainly top five.  The Portugese bun was like a wonderfully soft english muffin, slightly sweet like a Hawaiian roll, but still absorptive enough to handle the runny yolk and grease of the sausage on the sandwich.  Highly recommended with the Merguez patty.

Rose Quartz Crystal tea spoon... too cute, and yes the food was good too. The service and food was delicious and delightful. Beautiful Environment, Organic, Vegetarian, Deliciousness, Kindness and Cleanliness are all keys for me when picking a place to eat. Otway has nearly all of these. Thanks for the hospitality. One missing for me...I would like to see more organic options maked on you menu or some how communicated. I found out at the end of my meal by asking... I may have chosen a different meal had I known. What I eat was good either way. I had to ask and to my surprise, you all have a lot of things that are organic or sustainably sourced (like your wines, which I will be back to try). I wanted the waffle and it was 86 on the waffles the day I went. So you get a 4 stars, for the 86 on the waffles. - @GoddessProsper
One of our favorite places to go for a great dinner

Our favorite neighborhood hang for a superb happy hour with quality food and drink.. great natural wine selection, satisfying snacks and entrees and, if you're lucky like we were, $15 for a dozen oysters without a single speck of sand or grit in them. Love this place - highly recommended. Come early because the place is small and popular. Cheers!
A 5 star experience!

This most charming of charming spots is my favorite go-to in Clinton Hill for impeccable cocktails, a stunning dinner, and perfect pastries. Samantha has cultivated a lovely experience, and I am so grateful that this little oasis exists.

Great food. The first time I went was a weekday morning and the service was excellent. 5 stars. The second time was on a Saturday for brunch.  I called ahead and they had a table ready when I arrived with 3 other people 30 min later. Awesome! However, the place was packed and there was only one server. Maybe someone called in sick? It took at least 15 min before we were greeted by our server. He didn’t write down our order and made multiple mistakes. I will definitely go back as I think this past weekend may have been a fluke.
great brunch options and espresso drinks

Brunch = ** Date night/drink spot = *****  The $4 avocado that ruined everything....  So my boyfriend took me here on our first date and we had the best time ever. Stayed over two hours. Excellent wines and apps. Beautiful space. Led to a relash.  Fast forward 7 months later, I’m now living in SF but back in BK visiting him for the holidays. So we decide to try for brunch. MEGA disappointment.  $20 for their 2 egg breakfast with a side of avocado. Toast rock hard. Eggs cooked wrong. Bacon and potatoes over cooked. Fine not the best, could have dealt. But...  ...the small half of avocado served had black rotten spots and strings throughout. They did not even bother removing as there wouldn’t have been anything left. They did sprinkle it with sea salt, maybe hoping we wouldn’t notice. If I’m willing to pay $4 for a tiny portion of avocado, then I’m expecting it to be fricken perfect. My boyfriend’s egg sandwich was okay and the coffee was decent. Too many cheaper and amazing places in the neighborhood to f/w it again.
Lit
Coffee and pastries are great! So happy to see them open in the morning.

This place was humming when we showed up. After a short wait they found us a place to eat.  Excellent food. The duck was delicious. Innovative appetizers. The bartenders and servers were extremely knowledgeable and led us through a tasting adventure of natural wines from France. As a part time resident of Paris I found myself at home, very much like the local brasserie. Highly recommended.

(Translated by Google) Good food in a very pleasant, calm and young. Very open to the different schemes of each. Do not hesitate to ask questions.  (Original) Bonne nourriture dans un cadre très agréable, calme et jeune. Très ouvert aux différents régimes de chacun. Ne pas hésiter à poser des questions.
I need to go here more often than i do. The staff is amazingly kind. The decor is just so calm and gorgeous. And the food is great
They make a damn good cup of coffee. Only downside is that it’s a very expensive cup of coffee!

Stopped in for lunch and met Samantha, the sole owner and espresso slinger extraordinaire, who though very busy running the entire restaurant, found the time to chat and make me feel welcome. Learned about Australian coffee culture and we talked shop on pastry. Took home the savory bun (spinach & mushroom) and it was fire! Will absolutely come back every time I'm in the area. Go for lunch! Go for dinner! I'd say it's $$ not $$$. Absolutely worth it regardless.
Excellent food with service and coffee to match.
friendly staff and yummy oysters
Some of the best food in Brooklyn
The best Bloody Mary I have ever had. Great service and some delicious gems

Went for Sunday brunch. Chic decor, open, sunny, intimate. Coffee was hot and delicious, bright, slightly acidic, yet with some body. Their fresh baked bread is to die for and the French cheese starter was light, creamy, and magnifique. For the main dish I had the omelette—simple, cheesy, soft, and tasty. Staff were welcoming and friendly. And for dessert a chocolate plum cookie, rich and decadent. What a wonderful experience and lovely Brooklyn gem.
This is low key the best restaurant in Brooklyn.
Excellent happy hour, and a very good dinner.
Average food, good drinks, great bread.  Seriously overrated.  The Dorade is solid.

Atmosphere 5/5 Decor 5/5 Food 3/5 Wine list 4/5 Service 5/5  Lovely interior. Attractive crowd. Food was inconsistent, onion rings delicious. Wine list sprawling but with many gems. Very draft in front by the door.
Delicious food, good and attentive service, unbearably loud atmosphere, high price.
Great coffee here from 8am. And they do oat milk!
Delightful seasonal dishes at this welcomed addition to neighborhood. One of the best young restaurants in Brooklyn. Great wine list with a focus on natural and organic selection.
A bit pretentious for brunch

High concept, somewhat challenging seasonal food, heavy on offal and meaty dishes such as chicken hearts, lardo, venison tartare, and brined duck. Fun to sit at the bar and enjoy their wines and small but good craft beer selection.
OMG, food was great, OBVI, throw in charm and ambience and u got ur self a basket a biscuits u don’t wanna miss!
Incredible. Open one year and you know it will  only get better.
delicious food // mediocre service

Dreadful disappointment. Maybe they're good to regulars. My fish was saltier than the ocean and fishier too. After a few bites we returned the fish and oddly it appeared on the bill. The waiter, a nice fellow, told me the chef tasted it and said it was good. Must be me. No owning the salty fishy taste. Now that's SALTY behavior. Love tasting new flavors. Go to Olmsted or Wildair or wherever...forget about this unless you need more Salty in your life. Plenty here...
Love the place, a little pricey but good food.
Quality ingredients simply arranged; tasty but a bit too basic.
Very very disappointed. The food was terrible, service even worse.
We had a great brunch here. Super interesting food, well executed. Highly recommended.

First time there we shared four of the snacks and each were sublime. Literally looking forward to having a full meal there (although 4 snacks was enough to not need dinner afterwards).  Updated post-dinner in January ‘18: Great service, wonderful food. Go eat here!
Creative, forward thinking new American restaurant in Clinton Hill.
Good food, good service, nothing to write home about
Why the idea that fancy is better than good?

Unbelievably fantastic, in the vein of wildair (for foodies and natural wine lovers). The staff was unbelievably kind and fun even though we came in near closing. Every single thing we ate was amazing - generally, this place uses Mediterranean ingredients (chickpeas, mushrooms, fried cheese, etc) but innovates with the flavors.

Great date place. What stands out most is the the attention that the staff pays to their customers. You feel like a guest in their home. Love the beer options, but usually start with one of their creative cocktails. I usually opt for their tasty & unique starter menu. Stay for dinner and you're in for something that is hard to fake: raw talent in the kitchen. It comes across in the broad range of options and preparations catering to carnivorous savages and vegetarians alike and in their clear love of what they do. It's a local gem that delivers like a Manhattan dynastic mainstay or an Alpine kitchen before non-food was invented by Michael Keaton.

Wow. Beautifully designed space. So much attention has been put into every detail. I love the food. Aligote by the glass as an affordable delicious white burgundy option. Very smart guys. I heart you.
Aesthetically pleasing restaurant serving good food. My one qualm is that the entrees should be bigger or at least include some carbs.
If you don't like Otway, you are an idiot.

I'm not sure what Dan K. is talking about. His sad diatribe of a blowhard review is nothing short of a new parent temper tantrum. This place is great.  The food is constantly excellent and so is the service. The wine list and cocktails and inventive and unpretentious. Go here and remember why dining out is such a pleasure.

We're very happy with the steaks and wine ordered.  Staff are courteous and helpful. Restaurant is well maintained and clean. It's essential  to book for reservations as the place is small and popular round the area.  We'll return without doubt.

Overall, this experience was a disappointment.  As new parents, my wife and I were on a rare night out without the baby.  The meal immediately started off on the wrong foot.  After we ordered a couple appetizers and told the waiter we wanted to spend some time thinking about our entrees, the waiter came back from the kitchen to tell us that the Chef wants to know our full order and didn't want to do just the appetizers.  In other words, the Chef wanted to rush us.  This is shockingly unacceptable for even the lowliest restaurant.  I have worked as a waiter in a lot of restaurants, and I could not fathom the chef or myself saying anything to a guest that would make them feel rushed.  It's bad for business, as indicated by this review and the fact that we will not return.  The food was also pretty bad.  One of dishes we ordered was the uni (sea urchin) crepe.  Clearly, it was rancid. I have never tasted anything so foul in my whole life.  We told the waiter, who took back the dish.  BUT WE WERE STILL CHARGED FOR IT.  Again, I have had a lot of restaurant experience and when you're paying the kind of prices that Otway charges, you take the dish off the bill no questions asked.  Also, we asked the waiter about the dish before we ordered it and he didn't say anthing about a "strong" flavor.  When we said we didn't like it, he said it was a "polarizing" dish.  I know the dish was rancid.  But even if it wasn't, the waiter should have said the dish was "polarizing" before we ordered it.  Lastly, the drinks were boring.  I ordered some margarita-like cocktail and it tasted like someone sapped it of flavor.  It was muted and uneventful.  The service was bad.  The food quality was clearly bad, as demonstrated by the rancid dish.  And the cocktails are lackluster.
Come for the Sunday Lunch. The foie gras with sauternes actually comes with a glass of sauternes, which is brilliant because although they are excellent alone, together they offer far more.
Really enjoyed our dinner here. Fantastic venue.

Food was good to decent, blueberry tart  tasted like cheese whiz. Cocktails were great and the space was beautiful. Was hoping to like this place more, may come back but overall didn't meet expectations.

My favorite new place in Brooklyn. The little tasting menu at the bar is one of the best deals and a great look at the chefs thoughtful and clean style. Great little wine selection and a beautiful space to enjoy a meal.
Great place
Great food. Great cocktail. Great wine list. Will definitely be back!

Had a fantastic dinner last night at Otway. Pure flavors with many layers of complexity. Some of the best cooking I've encountered. Order the uni crepe with a glass of sparkling Jacky Blot Chenin Blanc.  Thank me later. Oh, and the service is on point. Bravo, Otway! 👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽
